  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the neglect of these high-order terms contributes to the bias, particularly on small scales.",
    "We denote N ′ as the intrinsic bias to distinguish it from the noise part, as this term persists even when delensing with a noiseless map.Then the delensed B-modes can be written as:B del = B obs -B temp = (B tens + B lens + B noise) -(B lens + N ′ + B temp N) = B tens + B noise -N ′ -B temp N = B tens + B noise + B res + B del N.(2.26)We have redefined two terms in the last line to align with an uniform format.",
    "Therefore, there are three components contributing to the delensed B-modes: the delensing residual N ′ (also referred to as B res or B del S hereafter), the intrinsic noise in observed B-modes B noise, and B temp N, the noise introduced during the lensing template construction procedure.",
    "We denote the latter two as the delensing noise.",
